<item>
            <title>[BEAM-13509] SQS reader uses shared client instance without coordinating shutdown (AWS SDK v2)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-13509</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The SQS client may be shared across readers of the same source instance without appropriate coordination when to close clients.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This affects the direct runner, I&apos;m not sure if other runners behave in a similar way (cc &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=aromanenko&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;aromanenko&quot;&gt;aromanenko&lt;/a&gt; ).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Investigate if this is also an issue in SDK v1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
